consolidate Liquibase into baseline + disable Liquibase temporarily

Triggered by a stale-volume boot failure: inventory-service hit
`liquibase.exception.DatabaseException: ERROR: relation
"inventory.goods_receipt_header" does not exist` while running an
old-baseline changeset against a fresh schema. The changeset history
had drifted out of sync with the rebaked baseline.

Stopping the bleeding: consolidate all 21 changesets into the
baseline, delete them, disable Liquibase entirely, document the
re-enable plan in dev-todo §2.15.

What shipped:

- 5 changeset effects folded into db/northwood_erp.sql that weren't
  already there:
  - inventory.stock_item.discontinued_at TIMESTAMPTZ (§1F.1)
  - finance.customer_invoice_header.flagged_for_collections BOOLEAN
    NOT NULL DEFAULT false (§1F.3)
  - reporting.available_to_promise_view.discontinued_at TIMESTAMPTZ
    (§1F.1)
  - reporting.customer_dashboard_status — new table with
    customer_id PK, status CHECK(active/inactive), deactivated_at,
    updated_at (§1F.3)
  - reporting.purchase_order_tracking_view.approved_at TIMESTAMPTZ
    (§1F.4)

- 16 other changesets verified redundant against the baseline
  (rebakes since shipping had already absorbed their effects).

- 21 changeset .sql files deleted across 7 service changes/ dirs.

- 7 master changelogs cleared to `databaseChangeLog: []` with a
  comment block explaining the temporary disable and the re-enable
  path.

- northwood.liquibase.enabled: false set in every service's
  application.yml (sales, inventory, manufacturing, purchasing,
  product, finance, reporting) with an inline comment pointing at
  dev-todo §2.15.

Why disable entirely rather than just empty the changelogs: with
empty changelogs, Liquibase still creates the databasechangelog +
databasechangeloglock bookkeeping tables on every boot — noise
that doesn't help while the baseline is canonical. The enabled
flag skips Liquibase entirely. Belt + braces — either alone would
suffice, both together makes the paused state harder to misread.

Re-enable criteria captured in dev-todo §2.15: baseline stops
rebaking, production-style deploys are on the horizon, migration
story exists for the demo dataset.

Verification: previously-failing boot path

```
docker compose down -v
docker compose up -d postgres
mvn -pl inventory-service spring-boot:run
```

now boots clean because Liquibase doesn't run.

No Java code changed — pure schema + config.

